Five people have died in a head-on collision between two vehicles on the N1 between Mookgopong and the Kranskop Toll Gate in Limpopo. Traffic officials say the road is expected to be closed for a few hours. Spokesperson Matome Moremi says motorists using the N1 near Mookgopong will be diverted to the R101. “We can confirm that this morning on the N1 around the area of Mookgopong, we had a head on collision between a Corolla LDV and a Polo Sedan. The road is going to be temporarily closed for about two to three hours. Traffic officials are on site trying to handle the scene,” says Moremi. Watch relate video below:  